name: keep_notes_permissions_batchDelete
description: Deletes one or more permissions on the note. The specified entities will immediately lose access. A permission with the `OWNER` role can't be removed. If removing a permission fails, then the entire request fails and no changes are made. Returns a 400 bad request error if a specified permission does not exist on the note.

parent.description: The parent resource shared by all permissions being deleted. Format: `notes/{note}` If this is set, the parent of all of the permissions specified in the DeletePermissionRequest messages must match this field.

BatchDeletePermissionsRequest.description: The request to remove one or more permissions from a note. A permission with the `OWNER` role can't be removed. If removing a permission fails, then the entire request fails and no changes are made. Returns a 400 bad request error if a specified permission does not exist on the note.

names.description: Required. The names of the permissions to delete. Format: `notes/{note}/permissions/{permission}`
